\/","url_meta":{"origin":36444,"position":0},"title":"Hadith on Charity: Expiation of sins for forgiving injury","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"March 22, 2020","format":false,"excerpt":"\u2018Ubadah ibn al-Samit reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cNo man suffers an injury to his body, and forgives it as charity, but that his sins will be expiated by the measure of his charity.\u201d Source: Musnad Ah\u0323mad 22701 Grade: Sahih li ghayrihi (authentic\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":37802,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2022\/05\/20\/expiation-sickness\/","url_meta":{"origin":36444,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Trials: Expiation of sins due to sickness","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 20, 2022","format":false,"excerpt":"Jabir reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cNo believing man or woman, nor Muslim man or woman, is afflicted with illness but that Allah will curtail some of their sins by it.\u201d Source: al-Adab al-Mufrad lil-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 508 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Al-Albani \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":27588,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/04\/15\/ramadan-expiation\/","url_meta":{"origin":36444,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Ramadan: Fasting this month expiates sins before it","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"April 15, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Sa\u2019id al-Khudri reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhoever fasts the month of Ramadan, acknowledging its limits and guarding it as it should be, then it will expiate the sins which came before it.\u201d Source: Musnad Ah\u0323mad 11524 Grade: Hasan (fair) according to\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":23456,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2016\/07\/12\/hadith-on-trials-sickness-expiation-sins\/","url_meta":{"origin":36444,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Trials: Sickness cause by sins, but Allah holds back","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 12, 2016","format":false,"excerpt":"Al-Bara' ibn 'Azib reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cThe veins and the eyes do not tremble with illness but due to sins, yet Allah repels even more.\u201d Source: al-Mu'jam al-S\u0323aghi\u0304r lil-T\u0323abara\u0304ni\u0304 1053 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Al-Albani \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0628\u064e\u0631\u064e\u0627\u0621\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0639\u064e\u0627\u0632\u0650\u0628\u064d \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":15344,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/07\/23\/dua-expiation-sins-assembly\/","url_meta":{"origin":36444,"position":4},"title":"H